Package br.com.kirgh.app.dtos

Record Class UserDTO

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
br.com.kirgh.app.dtos.UserDTO
public record UserDTO(@NotBlank(message="cannot be null or empty") @Size(min=2,max=150,message="size must be between {min} and {max}") @Pattern(regexp="[A-z\u00c3\u20ac-\u00c3\u00ba ]+",message="must contain only letters") String name, @NotNull(message="cannot be null or empty") @Past(message="must be before the current date") LocalDate birthDate, @NotNull(message="cannot be null or empty") UserGender gender, @NotBlank(message="cannot be null or empty") @Size(min=11,max=11,message="must have {min} characters") @CPF String cpf, @NotBlank(message="cannot be null or empty") @Email(message="is invalid") @Size(min=1,max=80,message="size must be between {min} and {max}") String email, @Valid UserRelationDTO relation) extends Record
This is a Java record class called UserDTO that represents a data transfer object for a user. It has six fields: name, birthDate, gender, cpf, email, and relation. Each field has validation annotations that specify constraints on the data that can be stored in the field. For example, the name field must not be blank, must be between 2 and 150 characters in length, and must contain only letters. The cpf field must not be blank, must be exactly 11 characters in length, and must be a valid Brazilian CPF number. The relation field is annotated with @Valid, which means that any nested objects of type UserRelationDTO will also be validated. This record class is used to transfer user data between different parts of an application or between different applications.
